VII. Advanced Moves

1. Pre-Framing (Frogman)

Before anything happens, define the rules subtly.

“I tend to think things through before I speak.”

Now:
Your silence later = strength

⸻

2. Frame Starvation

Refuse to feed weak frames.

People often collapse without reinforcement.

⸻

3. Controlled Ambiguity

Say just enough.

Let others:
	•	fill gaps
	•	reveal themselves
	•	commit prematurely

⸻

4. Delayed Detonation

Let a bad frame sit.

Correct it later when:
	•	stakes are higher
	•	audience is larger
	•	contrast is clearer

